title: Red Star Original Instant Dry Quick Rise Yeast
description: For bread machines & traditional baking. Fast acting dry yeast for bread machines.
instructions: Refrigerate or freeze after opening. Please refrigerate or freeze after opening. And use within 4 months after opening. Bread Machine Baking Tips: Use 1/2 tsp. Quick-Rise Yeast for each cup of flour. The suggested temperature for liquids is 80 degrees F for regular baking cycles. Follow manufacturer's directions for shorter cycles as warmer liquids may be required. Red Star QuickRise Yeast is great for traditional baking. Approximately 2-1/4 tsp. equal one 1/4 oz. yeast packet. Use a thermometer to determine liquid temperatures. Traditional Method: Dissolve 1 package of yeast in 1/4 cup of warm tap water (110-115 degrees F). Add 1/2 tsp. of sugar. Wait 5-10 minutes for mixture to foam (proof). Mixer Method: Blend yeast with flour and other dry ingredients. Warm liquids to 120-130 degrees F. Using liquids above 140 degrees F will harm the yeast.

title: Clabber Girl Multi Purpose Baking Soda
description: Clabber Girl Baking Soda makes a great leavening powder for your favorite recipes. This soda is also an environmentally safe dish and household cleaner. Sprinkle Clabber Girl Baking Soda over burnt-on food in pots and pans, let soak overnight, and scrub the next day. This soda removes dirt and grime from tile, tubs, floors, and counters as well.
instructions: Baking: Use your favorite recipes or visit clabbergirl.com for great baking ideas. Cleaning: Non-abrasive: Clabber Girl Baking Soda safely cleans away grease and soil on microwaves, refrigerators, sinks, counters, dishwashers (between loads), pots and pans, cutting boards and food containers. Just sprinkle on a damp sponge or cloth, wipe and rinse. Deodorizing: Sprinkle straight from the can to naturally eliminate odors or apply to a damp sponge, wipe and rinse. Great for refrigerators, freezers, carpets, upholstery and automobiles.
